Frequently used ping flags/options
==================================

>>	ping -I <interface-name> <dst>:- Specify interface name to send/receive ICMP

>>	ping -i <interval> <dst>:- Set gap between two ICMP. It can be more/less than 1

>>	ping -f <interface-name> <dst?>:- Flood network

>>	ping -s <size> <interface-name> <dst>:- Change Ping packet size. 
						If size = 100, Ping Bytes Sent = 128 Bytes 
						coz Ping Byte Sent is equal to Ping Packet Size(100 Bytes) 
						+ Ping Header Packet Size (28 Bytes)

>>	ping <hop1> <hop2> .. <hopN> <dst> :- Specify path of ping
	
>>	ping -R <dst> :- Record and print route of how ECHO_REQUEST sent and ECHO_REPLY received
